64.0	The_Screwtape_Letters	The Screwtape Letters	The Screwtape Letters is a satirical Christian apologetics novel written in epistolary style by C. S. Lewis, first published in book form in February 1942. The story takes the form of a series of letters from a senior demon, Screwtape, to his nephew, a junior "tempter" named Wormwood, so as to advise him on methods of securing the damnation of a British man, known only as "the Patient".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/c2/Thescrewtapeletters.jpg/200px-Thescrewtapeletters.jpg
